&quot;AAHHhhhhhh......... Home Sweet Home &quot;   

  (  in Canada, safe from the Floridian-ghost-box-researcher-eating-size-of-mice-cockroaches!!!)

Zack Widup &lt;w9sz@...&gt; wrote:

I saw palmetto bugs in Florida that were the size of mice. I thought to 
myself, &quot;That&#39;s just great. Flying cockroaches as big as mice!&quot;

I&#39;ve heard that in equatorial climates they get even bigger. I heard of 
fireflies in Sumatra that were a foot long. At least they are harmless!

Zack

On Wed, 21 May 2008, psfponies wrote:

&gt; OMG when I was in Cabo San Lucas the cockroachs were the size of rats! and there were several spider/bug things I have no idea what they were. I made sure I checked between the sheets before I crawled into bed everynight.
&gt;
&gt; Kay
&gt;
&gt;
&gt; Ron Lederer &lt;ronriko@...&gt; wrote:
&gt; Ah, a subject I can comment on with authority... killing ants and things that sting is my specialty here in Mexico...you&#39;ll love the simple answer...laundry detergent. I can tell you stories of tiny crazy ants to ants as large as half your thumb...tried all kinds of things like chlorine...acid...but a hand full of cheap, cheap, blue laundry detergent mixed in water will kill ants on the spot...dead, done, gone, ready for an EVP session. What a blessing since I am highly allergic to all pesticides. Getting ants out of an electrical system is another matter. I have them running along by house electrical lines and must wait for them to show their face before I soap em. Ron L
